      "body" : "That may work or not, depending which process is used to start the cmd.exe instance. If you use Windows explorer which recognizes the ENV changes and updates them internally then the changes will also be present in the cmd child porocess. However is a process is used as parent process which ignores the env changes then cmd will also get the old values. I had this case once on a system which used OpenShell as start menu replacement and OpenShell ignored env changes...",
